{"department_text": "Desktop Computers", "level": 1, "url": "http://www.tigerdirect.com/applications/Category/category_tlc.asp?CatId=6&name=Desktop Computers", "text": "Desktop Computers", "department_url": "http://www.tigerdirect.com/applications/Category/category_tlc.asp?CatId=6&name=Desktop Computers", "description_title": "Selecting a Desktop Computer", "keyword_count": {"selecting": 1, "desktop computer": 4, "computer": 7, "desktop": 9}, "description_wc": 220, "description_text": "Selecting a good desktop computer can be a daunting task. Not because there\u2019s a shortage of outstanding desktop PCs on the market. In fact, the opposite is true. The list of high-quality personal computers could fill a phone book \u2013 eMachines , Gateway , Cybertron , HP/Compaq , Visionman , iBuypower and their various models, to name just a few. For instance, are you searching for a media center personal computer? Are you looking for a desktop computer that your kids can use for schoolwork? Maybe you\u2019re operating a home business and you need a couple of desktop computers that can take care of all your administrative and networking demands. Some folks buy a desktop pc system as a spare - a backup in case the primary desktop PC is on the fritz. And many first-time desktop computer buyers are swayed by the sexiest ads and all the bells and whistles. While we believe that nearly everyone would benefit by owning a desktop, it\u2019s a good idea to take a step back and decide exactly what you\u2019re going to do with the desktop PC once you buy it. That way you avoid purchasing a computer system that\u2019s way too advanced for your needs, or conversely one that\u2019s ill equipped to meet your demands.", "keyword_density": {"selecting": "0.5", "desktop computer": "3.7", "computer": "3.3", "desktop": "4.2"}, "department_id": 35},
